# Dashboard Design Pattern

Follow this visual system for new pages, sections, and components.

## Theme Tokens First

- Always consume semantic tokens from `app/globals.css` (`--primary`, `--background`, `--card`, `--border`, `--muted`, sidebar and topbar tokens).
- Avoid hardcoded hex colors in components unless introducing a new shared token.
- Primary brand color is `#6E1A37`; primary text on brand is `#ECFAE5`.

## Layout Pattern

- Use a fixed left sidebar and top navigation shell for dashboard routes.
- Main content should sit on `--background`, and cards/sections on `--card` or `--surface`.
- Keep route pages thin and compose UI with container/view pattern under `app/common/pages/<route>/`.

## Shape and Radius

- Default radius scale is driven by global `--radius` and derived token sizes.
- Use medium corners for inputs/cards and larger corners for modals and major panels.
- Keep radius consistent across buttons, inputs, selects, cards, and modal surfaces.

## Typography

- Use Inter as the default sans font for all dashboard text.
- Keep heading/body contrast clear with token-based foreground colors.

## Dark Mode

- Every new UI section must remain readable in `.dark` mode.
- When adding new visual statuses (info/success/warning/error), define both light and dark token values in `app/globals.css`.
